        <div xml:id="AN6">
            <lg type="edition"><l>aripey cilampi ṉāmpalan toṭalai</l>
<l>yarampō ḻavvaḷaip polinta muṉkai</l>
<l>yiḻaiyaṇi paṇaittō ḷaiyai tantai</l>
<l>maḻaivaḷan tarūu māvaṇ ṭittaṉ</l>
<l>piṇṭa nelli ṉuṟantai yāṅkaṭ</l>
<l>kaḻainilai peṟāak kāviri nīttaṅ</l>
<l>kuḻaimā ṇoḷḷiḻai nīvey yōḷoṭu</l>
<l>vēḻa <choice><seg>veṇpaṉai</seg><seg>veṇpuṇai</seg></choice> taḻīip pūḻiyar</l>
<l>kayaṉā ṭiyāṉaiyiṉ mukaṉamarn tāaṅ</l>
<l>kēnteḻi lākattup pūntār kuḻaiya</l>
<l><choice><seg>neruṉa</seg><seg>neruṉai</seg></choice> <choice><seg><supplied>lā</supplied>ṭiṉai</seg><seg>yāṭiya</seg></choice> puṉalē yiṉṟuvan</l>
<l>tāka vaṉamulai yarumpiya cuṇaṅkiṉ</l>
<l>mācil kaṟpiṟ putalvaṉ ṟāyeṉa</l>
<l>māyap poymmoḻi cāyiṉai payiṟṟiyem</l>
<l>mutumai yeḷḷalaḵ <choice><seg>tamaikuvan</seg><seg>tamaikun</seg></choice> tilla</l>
<l>cuṭarppūn tāmarai nīrmutir paḻaṉat</l>
<l>tantūmpu vaḷḷai yāykoṭi mayakki</l>
<l>vāḷai mēynta vaḷḷeyiṟṟu nīrnāy</l>
<l>muḷḷaraip pirampiṉ mūtariṟ ceṟiyum</l>
<l>palvēṉ matti kaḻāa raṉṉavem</l>
<l>miḷamai ceṉṟu tavattol laḵtē</l>
<l>yiṉiyevaṉ <choice><seg>ceyvatu</seg><seg>ceytum</seg></choice> poymmoḻi yemakkē.</l></lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>There in Uṟantai with paddy in heaps,</l>
<l rend="indent">	of great liberal Tittaṉ who gives with the bounty of rain,</l>
<l rend="indent">	father of Aiyai with jewel-decked bamboo shoulders,</l>
<l rend="indent">	with anklets set with tinkling pieces, a water-lily wreath,</l>
<l rend="indent">	with forearms which sport saw-cut pretty bangles,</l>
<l>in the flood of the Kāviri in which the bamboo [pole] cannot stand<note place="foot">That is, the water is so deep that the pole propelling a boat or raft does not touch the ground.</note></l>
<l><choice><seg>you </seg><seg></seg></choice> <choice><seg>embraced, on </seg><seg>embracing </seg></choice> the white <choice><seg>Palmyra [raft], the bamboo [pole]</seg><seg>raft of bamboo</seg></choice> </l>
<l rend="indent">	along with her who is keen on you, with bright jewels, glorious with earrings</l>
<l><choice><seg>[and], </seg><seg></seg></choice> face content like [that of] an elephant bathing in a pond of the Pūḻiyar,</l>
<l rend="indent">	so that [your] flower garland is crushed against [her] rising graceful bosom,</l>
<l><choice><seg>you played in </seg><seg>during </seg></choice> <choice><seg>the floods </seg><seg>the floods in which you played </seg></choice> <choice><seg>yesterday.</seg><seg>yesterday,</seg></choice> </l>
<l rend="indent6"><choice><seg>	Today </seg><seg>	today </seg></choice> you come</l>
<l>[and] bow, repeating false, lying words</l>
<l rend="indent">	such as <choice><seg>“[my] son’s mother </seg><seg>“mother of [my] son </seg></choice> of faultless fidelity,</l>
<l rend="indent">	with beauty spots that budded on the beautiful breasts in [your] bosom”,</l>
<l>− don’t mock our age. We <choice><seg>shall </seg><seg>will </seg></choice> be content with it.</l>
<l>Like Kaḻāar of Matti with many spears,</l>
<l rend="indent">	where the old thicket of rattan with thorny trunks is tight</l>
<l rend="indent">	against the otter with sharp teeth who fed on Vāḷai fish,</l>
<l rend="indent">	disturbing the choice Vaḷḷai creepers with pretty tubers,</l>
<l>our youth is long gone.</l>
<l><choice><seg>Now what will </seg><seg>Now what will we do with </seg></choice> [your] lying <choice><seg>words do to us?</seg><seg>words, for ourselves?</seg></choice> </l></lg>
        </div>
    </body>
